 about colonial history and heritage, this book combines a variety of sources, an interdisciplinary approach, and an international scope to produce a cultural history of European imperial architecture across borders.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aImperialism and architecturezEuropexHistoryy19th century. 0aImperialism and architecturezEuropexHistoryy20th century. 4a20th century, c 1900 to c 1999. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aColonialism and imperialism. 4aEuropean history. 4aHeritage Studies. 4aHistory of architecture. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aModern History. 4aWestern Europe. 7aARCHITECTURE / Buildings / Public, Commercial & Industrial.2bisacsh  aColonial history, modern European history, heritage studies, architecture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048555291zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048555291/original  a978-3-11-076709-4 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA